        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I _think_ that the extended affliction items give you a variable number of extra ticks of damage, like from 1 to 3. As for Splurt, the damage of the last normal tick is used for the extra ticks -- it's not a continuation of the damage-increase curve. So using imaginary numbers, if normal Splurt ends with 75, 85, 95 ticks, the extended one might look like this:</P><P>75, 85, 95, 95<BR>75, 85, 95, 95, 95<BR>75, 85, 95, 95, 95, 95</P><P>I suppose you could get someone to buff you and then test it out by casting on yourself a few times to be sure. Good luck! :)</P><P>Aember</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
