        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         No, that is not how Splurt works. My suspision is that it reverts back to its first tick damage and begins to ramp from there for the extended period. It is hard to get a complete feel for Splurt using a PVP test, but when you convert back into PVE numbers, you end up with a 1700ish damage DOT. 1632, plus ticks of 12, 24, 36 gets you 1704HP. </P><P>For EAIII, the big winner is Funeral Pyre. Splurt would have been a great, but with the current mechanics, misses the boat. </P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
